4-D milestone firms partnering inspector + structural engineer multi-disciplinary teams + W-2 employee inspector working under brokerage or large multi-inspector firm. Mortgage qualifying under Fannie Mae B3-3.2-01 self-employed framework with 2-year personal returns + business returns if S-corp or partnership + CPA-prepared YTD P&L + Form 1084 cash-flow analysis adding back substantial business mileage (40K-60K+ annual miles at IRS standard rate $0.67/mile 2024 with depreciation portion approximately $0.30/mile recovered = $15K-18K for 50K miles) + business use of home Form 8829 + Section 179 expensing on inspection technology (thermal imaging cameras FLIR E5/E8/E76, DJI Mavic and Phantom drones, moisture meters, gas detection equipment, sewer scope cameras) + equipment depreciation + inspection software amortization at appropriate level. B3-3.4-02 partnership and S-corp documentation for entity-level synthesis. Bank Statement Non-QM 12-24 months business bank statement deposits with typical 50% expense ratio for high-mileage solo inspectors with substantial Section 179 + business use of home profile. P&L Statement Non-QM CPA-prepared profit and loss for established Certified inspector practices. Asset-Depletion Non-QM converting liquid portfolio balance to implied monthly income amortized over 360 months for senior inspectors transitioning. DSCR Debt Service Coverage Ratio Non-QM property rental income only qualifying with LLC ownership for inspector investment property portfolio scaling. Conventional Jumbo for HNW multi-inspector firm partners. Cash-Out Refinance for practice technology + drone + vehicle + equipment expansion. Construction-to-Permanent for inspectors building own custom home. 2022 Florida property insurance crisis driving wind mitigation + 4-point demand. SB 4-D milestone implementation 2025-2030 driving substantial recurring premium-fee inspection demand. Hurricane reconstruction inspection cycles through Andrew Charley Wilma Irma Michael Ian Idalia events. Florida HNW wealth migration sustaining HNW custom home inspection demand $5M-$25M+ price tiers. Multi-discipline specialty diversification through Ch 468 Part XV + Ch 468 Part XVI mold assessor + WDO termite + radon + FAA Part 107 drone pilot credentials supporting continuity narrative." canonical="https://stairwaymortgage.com/real-estate-professionals/home-inspector/">
